  "body": "I start a new erigon node and meet some problem.\r\n\r\n The first time I start with cli  \"./erigon --datadir /backup/erigon/\"  after 2 days, I read the doc  and  found this is a full node mode but My nvme space only 2T, maybe not enough for saving the data. so I delete the node  and  just want  keep block data,txhash transaction data and tx receipt data .\r\n I restart with new cmd ./erigon --datadir /backup/erigon/ --prune=hc --prune.h.older=0 --prune.c.older=0 --batchSize=2048\r\n\r\nthe current console log show:\r\nINFO[04-09|09:39:50.023] [6/16 Execution] Executed blocks        **number=5153872 blk/s=16.381** tx/s=1944.402 Mgas/s=106.164 gasState=1.229 estimated duration=236h6m4.025s batch=\"0.00 B\" alloc=\"1.45 GiB\" sys=\"6.22 GiB\"\r\nINFO[04-09|09:39:50.024] Committed State                          gas reached=7730150 gasTarget=6291456\r\nINFO[04-09|09:39:50.066] Committed State                          gas reached=8463786 gasTarget=6291456\r\nINFO[04-09|09:39:50.219] Committed State                          gas reached=9751852 gasTarget=6291456\r\nINFO[04-09|09:39:50.334] Committed State                          gas reached=7968751 gasTarget=6291456\r\nINFO[04-09|09:39:50.418] Committed State                          gas reached=7989208 gasTarget=6291456\r\n\r\neverything is happy except the blk/s speed.I simple estimate that it  nearly need 38 days to catch up with the latest block, It's so sad ...\r\nI humbly ask for advice, can I stop current sync process and restart it. I fear to lose prestage downloading header and body data.\r\nMy computer is Apple M1 16G Mem, 2T NVME.   how to speed up  Executed blocks stage. \r\nSincere thanks for all suggestions ：）",
